The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Kishore company plans unit in Haldia
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Kishore company plans unit in Haldia
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, Dec. 5: Kishore Chhabria-promoted Allied Blenders amp; Distilleries Pvt Ltd (ABD) is planning a facility in Haldia.         
	Today we have filed an application with the state government for its approval to set up a primary distillation unit in Haldia, said Deepak Roy, executive vice-chairman and chief executive officer of the company.         
	Roy said the distillery would have a capacity of 100 kilolitres per day, and the project involved an investment of between Rs 120 crore and Rs 125 crore. The distillery will make spirits from corn.         
	ABD  the maker of the Officers Choice whisky  has facilities at Aurangabad, and in Bangalore and Gurgaon. The fourth plant (in Haldia) is expected to come up in the next 12 to 18 months, Roy said.        
	Last December, ABD entered into a 50:50 joint venture with Henkell amp; Sohnlein of Germany to make the latters top-selling vodka brand, Wodka Gorbatschow. Henkell amp; Sohnlein India will have no manufacturing facility. We are importing the spirit from Germany and blending it here at our facility at Aurangabad, Roy said.        
	Roy hopes to sell between 75,000 and 100,000 cases of Wodka Gorbatschow during the current fiscal, grabbing a market share of 10 per cent in the premium segment. A 750-ml bottle of Wodka Gorbatschow will cost Rs 535.                                                                                                                                      
